[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1033[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Aggregate to Per-Week Cash Flow Forecasts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1034[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1035[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Take the per-claim, per-sample trajectories and produce per-week, per-payer cash flow forecasts with prediction intervals. The aggregation also produces a hospital-wide rollup and an aging-bucket-conditional summary so the finance team can see total expected cash, per-payer expected cash, and a confidence band.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1036[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1037[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1038[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def aggregate_forecasts(per_week_samples, aging_summary,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1039[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         horizon_weeks, as_of_dt):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1040[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Step 4: Aggregate Monte Carlo samples into per-week forecasts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1041[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1042[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     See pseudocode Step 4 in the main recipe. Returns a list of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1043[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     forecast records, each with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1044[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       forecast_week (ISO date of the week start),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1045[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       payer_id, expected_cash, p10_cash, p50_cash, p90_cash,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1046[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       sample_count, generated_at.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1047[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1048[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     forecasts = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1049[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     week_start_dates = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1050[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         as_of_dt.date() + timedelta(days=7 * w)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1051[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for w in range(horizon_weeks)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1052[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1053[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1054[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # All-payer aggregate per week. Aggregation is sample-wise:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1055[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # each sample's per-payer per-week values sum to a per-sample
